commit.message:
Noticed that the way templates render introduce whitespace before the
<?xml... line in html and xml documents.  This causes browsers to
ignore the encoding information held in that line.

I wrote a WhiteSpaceRemover with one removal operation to handle this
case.  Other operations can be added to the WhiteSpaceVisitor and
configured in settings.SITE_POST_PROCESSORS like so:
'public': {
        'hydeengine.site_post_processors.WhiteSpaceRemover': {
            'remove_document_leading_whitespace': True,
            }
        },

